The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 15, 2004 				 Taxman stalks Ketan firms 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								New Delhi, June 14: The income tax department has slapped a demand of Rs 1,385 crore on Big Bull Ketan Parekh and his group entities. This follows the JPC probe that led to the recovery of an undisclosed income of almost Rs 2,000 crore. 																								In the second action-taken report submitted by the finance ministry in Parliament, it has pointed out that the Central Board of Direct Taxes estimates the total demand raised in the Ketan Parekh group cases at Rs 1,365.37 crore. The interest on it adds up to Rs 41 crore. 																								The gross demand comes to Rs 1,406.37 crore. Out of this, there has been collection and reduction in appeal to the tune of Rs 21 crore. Therefore, the total outstanding demand in Ketan Parekh group cases is Rs 1,385 crore as on May 28, 2004. 																								The slapping of the notice comes after the income tax department conducted searches against Ketan entities after the scam surfaced in March 2001. 
